{"word":"G158 - αἴτιον - aítion - ah'-ee-tee-on - Cause","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">αἴτιον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">aítion</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">ah'-ee-tee-on</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Cause</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Noun Neuter / பெயர்ச்சொல் (அஃறிணை)</span>"},{"paragraph":"காரணர் - பெயரடை"},{"paragraph":"the author, that in which the cause of anything resides, causative, causing"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>Neuter of <a href=\"#/G159 - αἴτιος - aítios - ah'-ee-tee-os/159\">G159</a>; a <i>reason</i> or <i>crime</i> (like <a href=\"#/G156 - αἰτία - aitía - ahee-tee'-a/156\">G156</a>): - cause, fault.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}